(In reply to shankha banerjee from comment #18)

> public boolean hasTypeBit(int bit) {
> 	return false;
> }
> 
> What was the need for this?

This is so that you can eliminate the casts to reference binding, declaring
temporary variables to capture the cast results etc.

Essentially this block of code in you patch:

		if (originalLeftType instanceof ReferenceBinding && originalRightType instanceof ReferenceBinding) {
			ReferenceBinding leftR = (ReferenceBinding) originalLeftType;
			ReferenceBinding rightR = (ReferenceBinding) originalRightType;
			if (scope.compilerOptions().enableInvalidIdentityComparison &&
					rightR.hasTypeBit(TypeIds.BitUninternedType) && leftR.hasTypeBit(TypeIds.BitUninternedType)) {
				scope.problemReporter().invalidIdentityComparison(this, originalLeftType, originalRightType);
			}
		}


has become in mine:

if (compilerOptions.complainOnUninternedIdentityComparison && originalRightType.hasTypeBit(TypeIds.BitUninternedType) && originalLeftType.hasTypeBit(TypeIds.BitUninternedType))
			scope.problemReporter().uninternedIdentityComparison(this, originalLeftType, originalRightType);

due to this OOP technique.

Please work on the warning suppression capability. I'll release this
shortly.
